            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>The Spirit of Senatorial Eloquence</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>I should be recreant to my trust were I to stand here and say I did not
                    believe, upon my conscience and upon my heart, that no Black Republican can ever
                    be inaugurated President of the United States. And you call out your armies to
                    force us, and if we don't go into Boston into Winter quarters before you get
                    into Texas, then I am mistaken.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>Ex.</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>Article summarizes wild speech by Senator Wigfall of Texas on the rights of
                    slaveowners to the new territories and suggests that the Senator was completely
                    drunk during this speech on the Senate floor.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
        </page>
